      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>40 threads, <a href=item.html?item=6779&start=0>1</a> <a href=item.html?item=6779&start=25>2</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=item.html?item=6779&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105431411988253>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=6779&mid=105431411988253>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6779&mid=105431411988253>Getting To Kejar The Mighty</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6779&mid=105431411988253#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, May 30th 1:44 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=219852><span id= >Mesmerelda</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>OK have figured how to do this lately.<br><br>First of all you need to create a mule Cleric that worships Brell, probably a dwarf. Level him to level 4 and buy the spell divine aura.<br><br>Give the mule the robe and get him to grab a SoW and head for Paineel. When you zone in head thorugh the tunnel and you will appear outside at the edge of the Hole. Cast Divine Aura and immediately run over the edge. You should be alive when you hit the bottom (#7 on EQ Atlas map). Stay away from Master Yael if he is up, otherwise all the other elementals, stone golems and flighty fiends will ignore you, regardless of what they con to you. Head for the only exit out of the area which I believe is to the West.<br><br>Now the only mob you really need to keep clear of is a Ratman. Which roams either end of the two tunnels and in the middle area.<br><br>Follow the upward sloping tunnel until you come to the exit stay close to the right hand side wall and avoid the revenant (Erudite ghost looking thing) as you make a right turn. Run up the slope and there should be another tunnel entrance to your left. Enter the tunnel and follow it until you come to a pool with Jaeil the Wretched (#8 EQ Atals map). Hopefully you haven't come across the ratman yet, you should wait here until you see him coming. When he appears jump into the right hand pool and swim as far as way from the path as possible until the ratman leaves. Once he does jump out and continue on up the tunnel. From hear it's all clear sailing. When you get to the end of the tunnel take the right and make your way to the area above #11 on the EQ Atlas map. Enter the building and make your way up the stairs until you get to Kejar the Mighty. Good luck to all of you attempting it. Got one robe and a chunk of metal so far hehe. =)</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
